Re: Mr. Bear, Mr. Bear - lyric question tranditional Jp Song
by blutorange » Fri 04.08.2011 1:52 pm oldwordstudy wrote:Line 3 kuma san kata ashi ageteWhat is "kata" doing here, since i already knew that "ashi" means "leg"?It's 「片足」, one leg, 片 meaning "one (of a pair)".chikara wrote:Kikoete is "to be heard" or "to be audible" not "can hear" the "kuru" gives the meaning "can be heard". I would say -ete (from 得る) gives the "can" and kuru the "be ~ed" part. Anyway.Blutorange
